The Department of State Services (DSS) has confirmed raiding the residence of Sunday Igboho, self-acclaimed Yoruba activist, in Ibadan, Oyo State capital.. At a briefing on Thursday night, the secret police said Igboho is currently on the run. Peter Afunanya, spokesman of the DSS, paraded 12 of Igboho’s supporters arrested during the operation. He also displayed charm, weapons, telephone and passports which he said were recovered from Igboho’s house. Below are pictures. 